author: dlr
msg: * Makefile.in
(swig-java-ext): Adjusted target to swig all Java source code into
the org.tigris.subversion.swig package.  As the generated code is
currently hideous, dumping it into a single location which users of
the API won't have to look at seems reasonable.  It's possible that
cleaner code can be generated and this decision should be
revisited, but right now I don't know enough about SWIG to say
definitively.
Changed module prefix from "svn_" to "Subversion".  I'd be open to
"SVN" instead, but "svn_" generated a source file with name
"svn_.java".
(swig-java-ext-clean): All generated sources are now under the
$(SWIG_SRC_DIR)/java/ directory -- no need to look for *.java files
mixed directly into the revision controlled portion of the WC.
